  "texts": [
    "Although emergence establishes the foundation for habit formation, it also causes unforeseeable ethical risks to LLMs, including the risk of being manipulated to produce harmful content.",
    "Homogenization can further consolidate and amplify these emergent ethical issues.",
    "Moreover, the unpredictability of ethical risks and the possibility of human malfeasance suggest that the ethical challenges associated with LLMs extend beyond algorithms and data-related concerns.",
    "They also involve large-scale concerns that are deeply intertwined with socio-economic systems.",
    "Finally, since LLMs inherently lack self-awareness, their moral competence essentially depends on alignment with human guidance and regulation."
  ],
